Points:
- Kafka is a high througput distributed messaging system.
- It is created by LinkedIN
- Open source tool
- Now managed by a private Company named 'Confluent'
- It has horizontal scalability (Can scale to millions of messages per second)
- High performance


Use Cases of Kafka:
- Messaging System
- Activity Tracking
- Metrics gathering
- Application logs gathering
- Stream processing


Examples:
- Netflix uses Kafka to apply recommendations in real time while you are watching shows
- LinkedIn uses it to recommend connections


